  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-05 00:55 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC shelf near break, ETH defense worsens\n\n**Task:** Run P1 copy intelligence after P4 showed BTC >80K and fast RANGE-UP but slow STOP unchanged. Check whether BTC reclaims +23M, loses +20M, or stays fragile; verify ETH/SOL/HYPE hedge posture.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Ran `/home/ubuntu/clawd/scripts/copy-intel-tracker.py`: **BTC 5L/3S**, **ETH 1L/6S**, **SOL 2L/6S**.\n- Current top-book notional: BTC **+$20.34M net long**, ETH **-$18.40M net short**, SOL **-$5.87M net short**, HYPE **-$9.94M net short**.\n- BTC net weakened **+$22.26M \u2192 +$20.34M**, now only **+$0.34M** above the +20M shelf. BTC breadth stayed **5L/3S**.\n- `anon-0xecb6` BTC LONG trimmed **$11.55M \u2192 $10.05M**, still above $10M but barely. `anon-0x57dd` trimmed **$2.39M \u2192 $2.09M**. `beatmaker1` BTC short increased **$113.7K \u2192 $253.2K**. `anon-0xf5d8` remains BTC short **$271.2K**. `anon-0xfc66` held **$5.23M** and `anon-0x8fcc` held **$3.53M**.\n- Cross-asset context worsened: ETH worsened **-$17.99M \u2192 -$18.40M**, breadth **2L/5S \u2192 1L/6S**; SOL remains heavily defensive near **-$5.87M**, breadth **2L/6S** with tiny longs only; HYPE remains about **-$10M**, breadth **3L/6S**.\n- `ecb6` remains hedged: BTC LONG **$10.05M** vs ETH SHORT **$16.75M**, SOL SHORT **$4.88M**, HYPE SHORT **$2.19M**.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p1-btc-shelf-near-break-eth-defense-worsens-2026-05-05-0055.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** BTC copy remains technically shelf-holding, but only barely. The prior firmness faded quickly: `ecb6` trimmed ~$1.5M BTC, BTC short notional rose, and ETH defense worsened to 1L/6S. This is a warning state: BTC-specific bullish is still valid by threshold, but a break below +20M would flip P1 broadly defensive.\n\n**Decision:** Keep